  "raw_text": "\n\n# I AM THE CHANGE\n\n## Scholarship Program \u2014 Home Visit Questionnaire\n\nTeam Everest | Confidential\n\n|                  |                                      |                |\n|------------------|--------------------------------------|----------------|\n| Volunteer Name:  | Co-Volunteer Name:                   | Date of Visit: |\n| VISUDHA BOOBALAN | ABDULLA TIPPU<br>SULTAN INAYATHULLAH | 23/06/2026     |\n\n## Section 1 \u2014 Student Profile\n\n### 1.1. Application ID\n\nEnter Application ID\n\nTEMP- 2026- 8803\n\n### 1.2. Student Full Name\n\nEnter full name\n\nSABARINATHAN K\n\n### 1.3. Gender\n\n\u2612 Male \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Female \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Others\n\n## Section 2 \u2014 Family Background\n\n### 2.1. Family Status\n\n\u2610 Single Parent \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Parentless \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Having both parents\n\n### 2.2. Relationship Details (if applicable)\n\n| Year of Death / Separation | Reason for Death / Separation |\n|----------------------------|-------------------------------|\n|                            |                               |\n|                            |                               |\n\n### 2.3. Is Father/ Mother photograph kept at home?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2612 No\n\n### 2.4. Government ID Verified (Ration Card / Aadhaar / Driving Licence / Voter ID)\n\n\u2612 Aadhaar Card \u2612 Ration Card \u2612 Driving Licence \u2612 Voter ID\n\n\u2610 Other: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n### 2.5. Family Members\n\n| Name          | Age | Education                       | Occupation | Annual Income |\n|---------------|-----|---------------------------------|------------|---------------|\n| P. KATHIRESAN | 47  | SSLC                            | MECHANIC   | \u20b9 72,000      |\n| K. REVATHI    | 41  | SSLC                            | HOUSEWIFE  | 0             |\n| K. BHAVANA    | 18  | COLLEGE<br>1 <sup>st</sup> YEAR | -          | -             |\n|               |     |                                 |            |               |\n\n## Section 3 \u2014 Housing Condition\n\n### 3.1. House Ownership\n\n\u2610 Own \u2612 Rented\n\n#### \n\n--- Page 2 ---\n\n3.1.1 If rented, what is the rent amount?\n\nRent amount\n\n\u20b9 7,000 MONTHLY\n\n### 3.2. Type of Home\n\n\u2612 Individual \u2610 Private Apartment \u2610 Housing Board \u2610 Line House \u2610\n\nOthers: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n### 3.3. Type of Ceiling\n\n- \u2610 Roof (Kurai) \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Tiled \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Asbestos / Sheet \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Concrete\n\n### 3.4. Number of Bedrooms\n\nEnter number\n\n1\n\n#### \n\n--- Page 3 ---\n\n3.4.1 Type of Bedroom\n\n- \u2612 Separate Bedroom \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No Separate Bedroom\n\n### 3.5. Bathroom\n\n- \u2612 Separate \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Common for Apartment\n\n### 3.6. Kitchen Type\n\n- \u2612 Separate Kitchen \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Hall with Kitchen\n\n## Section 4 \u2014 Financial Background\n\n### 4.1. Assets at Home (tick all that apply)\n\n- \u2612 Washing Machine \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Fridge \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 AC \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 LED TV \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Two-Wheeler \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Car\n- \u2612 Smartphone \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Separate Wi-Fi \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Others: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n### 4.2. Amount of Last Electricity Bill\n\nAmount in \u20b9\n\n\u20b9980\n\n### 4.3. Do you own any other assets/properties in the name of grandparents, parents, or student?\n\n- \u2612 Yes \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No\n\n4.3.1 If yes, list their properties:\n\n| Property Description               | Owner Name                   | Approximate Value |\n|------------------------------------|------------------------------|-------------------|\n| Land, (640 Sq Ft)<br>Kovilambakkam | PRABHAKARAN<br>(GRANDFATHER) | \u20b9 20,00,000       |\n|                                    |                              |                   |\n\n4.4. Apart from your job, is there any other source of income?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2612 No\n\n4.4.1 If yes, list other sources of income:\n\n| Source of Income | Amount |\n|------------------|--------|\n|                  |        |\n|                  |        |\n\n4.5. Income Type\n\n\u2610 Monthly \u2610 Daily \u2610 Weekly \u2612 Ad-Hoc\n\n4.6. Do you have any loans?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2612 No\n\n4.6.1 If yes, share Loan Purpose, Amount Taken, and Pending Loan Amount:\n\n| Sr. No. | Loan Purpose | Loan Amount Taken | Pending Loan Amount |\n|---------|--------------|-------------------|---------------------|\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n\n4.7. If you choose any college, how much is the college fee?\n\nAmount in \u20b9\n\n\u20b9 90,000 YEARLY\n\n4.8. If the college fee is higher, how will you manage it?\n\nLOANS / SCHOLARSHIP\n\n4.9. If you do not receive this scholarship, how will you pay the fees?\n\nLOANS\n\n## Section 5 \u2014 Health Information\n\n5.1. Does the student have any health issues?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2612 No\n\n5.2. If yes, list the health issues:\n\nDescribe health issues\n\n## Section 6 \u2014 Student Commitment\n\n6.1. Will you study college for three years without any obstacle?\n\nYES\n\n6.2. If we have a training program within 15 km from your home, can you come?\n\n\u2612 Yes \u2610 No \u2610 Maybe\n\n6.3. Are you ready to send your son/daughter to weekly skill development classes on Sundays (16 classes a year)?\n\n\u2612 Yes \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No\n\n## Section 7 \u2014 Scholarship Information\n\n7.1. Has the student received or applied for any other scholarships for their UG degree?\n\nNONE\n\n## Section 8 \u2014 Volunteer Observation\n\n8.1. What is your opinion about the student, their family members, and their living condition?\n\nThe student's father is a mechanic and does not receive income on a fixed basis. He is the sole earning member of the family. Also, they are living in a rented house (small). They have no property other than their grandfather's land in which there are multiple heirs.\n\n8.2. Will you recommend this student for this scholarship?\n\n\u2612 Yes \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Not Sure\n\n8.3. Any other comments you want to share?\n\nThe student needs the scholarship the most to pay for their college fees and complete his studies without hindrance.\n\nVolunteer Signature\n\nB. vijeth\n\nCo-Volunteer Signature\n\n[Signature]",
